Full Description: The 1947 Partition Archive is a grassroots non-profit organization dedicated to documenting, preserving and sharing eye witness accounts from all ethnic, religious and economic communities affected by the Partition of British India in 1947. We provide a platform for anyone anywhere in the world to collect, archive and display oral histories that document not only Partition, but pre-Partition life and culture as well as post-Partition migrations and life changes. As another year unfolds, memories of Partition float further back in time. Many thousands risk disappearing forever this year, leaving unfilled gaps in the collective memory of our cultural inheritance. We teach and empower citizens around the world to record memories of Partition on video. We believe the process of recording a story builds trust and empathy, as well as sharing of knowledge in the most intimate way possible.

Description: The Eno Center for Transportation is a nonprofit think tank in Washington.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: The Eno Center for Transportation (Eno) was founded in 1921 by William Phelps Eno (1859-1945), who pioneered the field of traffic management in the United States and Europe. Mr. Eno sought to promote safe mobility by ensuring that traffic control became an accepted role of government and traffic engineering a recognized professional discipline. Eno focuses on all modes of transportation, with the mission of cultivating creative and visionary leadership for the sector. They pursue this mission by supporting activities in three areas: professional development programs, policy forums, and publications. Eno is a non-profit charitable foundation, recognized by the IRS as a 501(c)(3). It is an operating foundation and does not make grants. About half of the Foundation’s work is supported by its endowment; the remainder is supported by tuition and fees, contracts, and publication sales. In order to make the best use of its resources, the Foundation often works in partnership with government agencies, professional organizations, and other private organizations.

Description: PreMedicus® is a precision population health management startup using Digital Medicine & AI for better & cheaper healthcare.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: PreMedicus® LLC is an Atlanta digital medicine start-up focused on helping people rapidly understand and more accurately solve pressing medical problems using their own mobile devices.   Our enterprise quality platform uses proprietary algorithms developed by our founder, seasoned Critical Care physician and National Medical Honor Society member Dr. Tony Kimani, to analyze the user’s health concerns in the way that top doctors think.  We then add the power of traceable artificial intelligence analysis and machine learning to develop deep hyper-personalized population health insights to forewarn and prevent future illness. We offer a customizable cloud-based SaaS solution for large population health management enterprises and governments seeking to reduce avoidable urgent care and ER visits, promote patient engagement in their own health, and offer acutely ill adults accurate health advice and timely referral to appropriate health resources.  PreMedicus® PH is a proprietary precision population health management platform protected by copyrights and trade secrets that meets the needs of large population health enterprises and comprises:       1.	 PreMedicus® ER, a user-friendly patient facing mobile app that accurately triages over 100 medical conditions, provides real-time patient-specific triage advice with in-app 911 call capability, and GPS guidance to nearby pharmacies, physician offices, urgent care facilities or emergency departments as deemed appropriate by the Triage Engine.  PreMedicus® ER can be integrated with telemedicine platforms and the digital front door of urgent care, ER and retail pharmacy facilities.  Please follow this link to watch a short demonstration video:  https://drive.google.com/file/d/1QsLjk3nDRh8H4-WlW7jjbiYRmVR-TUxv/view?usp=sharing 2.	PreMedicus® ASV, an adult sick visit management app for in-person healthcare that automates all aspects of the patient-provider interaction.  Both parties link securely to our cloud platform on this intuitive mobile app that collects information in parallel, and reformats clinical and billing data in real time to reduce staff work burdens and exposure risks, and to improve both patient and provider experience. 3.	Our integrated Education Engine providing targeted up to date health maintenance and disease education through partnerships with world-class digital health libraries. 4.	Our proprietary Risk Engine that analyzes a particular individual's probability of contracting common diseases, and developing early or late complications of active illnesses. 5.	Our Machine Learning Engine using artificial intelligence to analyze patient data and non-invasive digital biometrics to uncover sub-clinical symptoms, refine our medical algorithms, and provide our enterprise customers with population-based predictive analytics; 6.	Our Population Health Engine, a customizable dashboard for reviewing comprehensive population level health data in summary form. Population managers have direct visibility to their population’s metrics, and can quantify the health and business advantages delivered by our platform.
